org.rsna.ctp.stdstages.anonymizer.xml

Class XmlPathElement

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.rsna.ctp.stdstages.anonymizer.xml.XmlPathElement

  • public class XmlPathElement
extends java.lang.Object
    A class to assist in walking down an XML path, with support for wildcards. A path consists of a starting node and a series of path segments coded as a text string in the format of an XPath expression, except that instead of predicates, path segments can have wildcards or predicate-like qualifiers as described in the documentation for the segment field below.

    An XmlPathElement is parsed into:

    • node: the parent node from which the path proceeds
    • path: the full path from the parent node to the end
    • segment: the first step along the path after the parent node
      • remainingPath: the rest of the path after the segment.

      • getValue

        public java.lang.String getValue()

        Returns:
        the text value of the parent node.

      • setValue

        public void setValue(java.lang.String value)

        Parameters:
        value - the text value to assign.
